{"key":"post-11813610","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11813610</id>\n<content>For best results, you want light coming in from five sides.&amp;nbsp; That means a clear tub.&amp;nbsp; That doesn't mean an opaque tub won't work, it means a clear one will work better.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For lighting, if you mean incandescent by 'globe' it's a poor choice.&amp;nbsp; Get a fluorescent lamp in the 6500K range for best results, and/or put the tub near a bright window. The dark period need not be totally dark or uninterrupted.&amp;nbsp; If you need to turn on your room light to see at night, it won't hurt the mushrooms, but they do need a normal day/night schedule for best performance. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Put the terrarium on a table and elevate it off the table with blocks to allow air to circulate around all six sides.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11817635</next>\n<prev>11812854</prev>\n<first>11780959</first>\n<last>11817785</last>\n<when>1263311965</when>\n<utime>01/12/10 05:59 PM</utime>\n</post>"}